cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed model fitting and proposes iterative methods for solving global sub-problems over a distributed dataset.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions fitting linear classifiers and sparse linear models to datasets.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses strategies for solving least-squares over massive datasets without putting all the data in one place.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper proposes iterative methods for solving global sub-problems and discusses least-squares methods.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses strategies for efficient distributed computing.
